      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Monday ¶ The letter from G. S. Fort to M, cited by M below, was written on a Sundayand would have been delivered the following day;the present letter has been dated on that basis. ¶  ¶ This morning, d...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.10.10</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Alexander Macdonald</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A38, Papers of the Royal Geographical Society of Australasia (Victorian Branch), Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Monday</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The letter from G. S. Fort to M, cited by M below, was written on a Sunday<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and would have been delivered the following day;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the present letter has been dated on that basis.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This morning, dear Mr Macdonald, I received the byefollowing letter from Mr Fort.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>G. S. Fort to M, 9 October 1887.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Will you kindly give your opinion thereon, so that we may have the advantage of the viceregal presense.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr Forbes epistle,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See H. Forbes to M, 5 September<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1887<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 87-09-05a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I suppose, you like to place before the Council, who can give then full force to your reply. I will merely acknowledge the letter pro forma,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to H. Forbes, 26 October 1887.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>except explaining that the specific elaboration of the plants even in Europe would take a great deal of time. Whether he has<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">all</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the notes (some he has) or not, cannot affect his sending a short report and a sketch map. A<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">full</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>list of the plants would be only suitable as an appendix for his<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">new volume</hi>
               </seg>, the printing of which (so far as I am aware) has not even yet commenced.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Forbes's only known book is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>H.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Forbes (1885), published in both London and New York editions.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>There are appendices to each section, with lists of plants<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and some animal groups<space unit="chars" quantity="3"/>after each section of the book, with a major<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Appendix VI,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>pp 497-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>523,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a 'Prodromus Florae Timorensis'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by specialist authors<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>including descriptions of several new species.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We shall of course be delighted, to have Mr Giles, if he will be ready within a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">reasonable time</hi>
               </seg>,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">and</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I will telegraph to him at Port Darwin to that effect, if<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">you</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>concur in this. Or a telegram to that effect I could send him yet to Brisbane.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ernest<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Giles went to the Kimberley district, WA, in 1887, travelling by 'the eastern route', to prospect for gold. See M to S. Davenport, 5<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>October<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1887 (in this edition as 87-10-05a),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to S. Davenport,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>16 October 1887.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
